```

2. **Generate PDF via Shell tool:**
   ```bash
   cd /Users/dmytrolozynskyi/Documents/cv && python3 generate.py "[Job Title] at [Company]"
   ```

3. **Open PDF automatically via Shell tool:**
   ```bash
   open /Users/dmytrolozynskyi/Documents/cv/output/Dmytro_Lozynskyi_[sanitized_filename].pdf
   ```
   This will open the PDF in Preview (macOS) so user can visually see the formatted CV.

4. **Ask for confirmation:**
```
üìÑ PDF preview opened! Please review the formatted CV.

Does this look good? 
- Say "yes" or "looks good" if ready to apply
- Tell me what to adjust if you want changes
```

### STEP 6: Handle User Response
- If user approves: Confirm PDF is ready to apply
- If user requests changes: Re-edit cv_master.yaml, regenerate PDF, and open again
- Iterate until user is satisfied

## Important Notes
- This is a NEW chat for each job application
- User has 50 applications to do - be efficient
- Default to founder positioning for PM roles
- Every bullet needs a metric
- If metric is unknown, use [VERIFY: X] placeholder
- Follow TAILORING_GUIDE.md for all formatting decisions
